The article discusses how manufacturers in the United States are expected to benefit from the recently passed tax reform. It states that with the new tax code, manufacturers will be able to hire more workers, create well-paying jobs, invest in communities, and increase the income of manufacturing workers. The article also mentions that a survey conducted by the National Association of Manufacturers (NAM) showed that most respondents believed that tax reform would lead to business growth, increased investments, and the hiring of more workers. The article concludes by highlighting the promise of tax reform and the commitment of manufacturers to deliver on that promise.